<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Sample Webpage</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #0056b3;
        }
        p {
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Welcome to My Sample Webpage</h1>
    <p>This is a basic example of an HTML document.</p>
    <p>It includes a heading, a couple of paragraphs, and some inline CSS for styling.</p>

    <h2>Key Elements Used:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code>: Declares the document type.</li>
        <li><code>&lt;html lang="en"&gt;</code>: The root element of an HTML page, specifying the language as English.</li>
        <li><code>&lt;head&gt;</code>: Contains meta-information about the HTML document (e.g., title, character set, viewport settings, styles).</li>
        <li><code>&lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;</code>: Specifies the character encoding for the document.</li>
        <li><code>&lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"&gt;</code>: Configures the viewport for responsive design.</li>
        <li><code>&lt;title&gt;</code>: Sets the title that appears in the browser tab or window title bar.</li>
        <li><code>&lt;style&gt;</code>: Contains CSS rules for styling the HTML elements.</li>
        <li><code>&lt;body&gt;</code>: Contains the visible page content.</li>
        <li><code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;h2&gt;</code>: Heading elements of different levels.</li>
        <li><code>&lt;p&gt;</code>: Defines a paragraph of text.</li>
        <li><code>&lt;ul&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;li&gt;</code>: Unordered list and list item elements.</li>
        <li><code>&lt;code&gt;</code>: Used to display a piece of computer code.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>More about HTML</h3>
    <p>HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard markup language for documents designed to be displayed in a web browser. It can be assisted by technologies such as Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) and scripting languages such as JavaScript.</p>

</body>
</html> 
